Fresh Pi session: WRITE ONE CONCRETE FAILING TEST.

Inputs:
- Selected scenario: latest {{run.dir}}/tdd/current-scenario-*.json
- Approved use case: latest file under {{run.dir}}/use-case/
- Repository constraints: {{run.dir}}/design/repository-constraints.md
- Prior issues: {{run.issues-file}}
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

The current working directory is the isolated worktree.

Goal:
Turn exactly the selected scenario into a real runnable automated test with meaningful assertions.

Rules:
- Edit test code only. Do not implement or change production behavior.
- Do not turn any other pending scenario into a concrete test, assertion, fixture mutation, or negative control. A control may demonstrate already-supported behavior only.
- The selected scenario itself must account for the red result. If it is already satisfied, report failure instead of manufacturing red by asserting a different missing behavior.
- Interface decisions required to express this one test are allowed; avoid implementation design.
- Derive expected values independently. Never paste actual computed output into expectations merely to pass.
- Include setup, invocation, and assertions using repository conventions.
- A compile/interface failure is acceptable only when it directly demonstrates the selected missing interface; unrelated syntax, fixture, dependency, or environment failures are not meaningful red.
- Run the narrow test command once to establish the observed failure, but leave independent execution to the next process node.
- Create a version-1 focused-check manifest. Prefer an argv-array command; a compound shell command must be an explicit string with `"shell": true`.
- Include a bounded timeout and one or more stable `red.output_contains` markers that identify the intended test/assertion failure rather than generic error text.
- Reuse the selected scenario id exactly. The same command must be suitable for red now and green after implementation.
- Do not commit, push, or create a PR.

Write:
- Report including test file/name, interface choices, exact observed failure, and expected failure reason: {{run.dir}}/tdd/test-{{run.round}}.md
- Focused check: {{run.dir}}/tdd/check-{{run.round}}.json
- Status: {{run.dir}}/tdd/write-test-status-{{run.round}}.json
- On failure: {{run.dir}}/tdd/write-test-issues-{{run.round}}.json

Focused-check shape:
{"version":1,"scenario_id":"SC-001","id":"focused-scenario-001","command":["npm","test","--","specific-test"],"timeout_seconds":120,"red":{"expected_exit":"nonzero","output_contains":["specific-test","expected assertion text"]}}

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"one concrete test and focused check manifest written","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"test is not yet a meaningful runnable red","issues_file":"tdd/write-test-issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
